<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Based on ITS sequences, 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. vacillans" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is genetically well distinct from other 
<taxonomicName class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. However, it may be confused with several other species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pykaelae &amp; Myllys" authorityYear="2020" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria vacillans" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most difficult to separate from 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. cavernarum" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="cavernarum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. cavernarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. difficilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In these three species, dark lines between contiguous conspecific thalli are never present. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pykaelae &amp; Myllys" authorityYear="2020" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria cavernarum" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cavernarum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria cavernarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have an involucrellum seldom exceeding half of the exciple (and then only in a minority of perithecia). The exciple of 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sometimes pale (although usually dark). The spores tend to be slightly broader in 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. vacillans" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than in 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, specimens of 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. vacillans" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without dark lines and with a short involucrellum may not be possible to separate from 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. cavernarum" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="cavernarum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. cavernarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by morphology. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. vacillans" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a deep reaching involucrellum may not be separable from 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. difficilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
if dark lines are absent. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pykaelae &amp; Myllys" authorityYear="2020" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria vacillans" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may also be confused with 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. devergens" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="devergens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. devergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. kuusamoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="kuusamoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. kuusamoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. epilithea" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="epilithea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. epilithea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. muralis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="muralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. muralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pykaelae, Kantelinen &amp; Myllys" authorityYear="2020" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria kuusamoensis" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="kuusamoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria kuusamoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an involucrellum usually exceeding half of the exciple, larger spores and dark lines are rather rare. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nyl., Flora 55: 362" authorityYear="1872" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria devergens" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="devergens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria devergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has larger spores and the involucrellum is usually absent or sometimes apical. 
<taxonomicName class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria epilithea" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="epilithea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria epilithea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
